    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Bindings in a simple style featuring tooled republican motifs and symbols, commissioned in large quantities by the English republican Thomas Hollis, who gave away collections of books bound in this way to universities and libraries in Europe and America to disseminate and promote republican beliefs.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099620/Legacy AAT data</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Boekbanden in een eenvoudige stijl, bewerkt met republikeinse motieven en symbolen, in grote aantallen vervaardigd in opdracht van de Engelse republikein Thomas Hollis, die verzamelingen van op deze wijze gebonden boeken schonk aan universiteiten en bibliotheken in Europa en Amerika om het republicanisme te verspreiden en de bevorderen.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>一種風格簡易的裝幀法，以壓印的共和派圖案與圖像為特色，由英國共和黨員霍利斯（Thomas Hollis，1720-1774）負責大量印製，將此類書籍捐贈給歐美各大學與圖書館，藉此宣揚共和黨思想。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000079740/AS-Academia Sinica data (2014-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
    </Descriptive_Notes>
